<subSubSection id="C34015E2FF84FF98FDB4D36FBC2DFAC2" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BE54669FF84FF98FDB4D36FBB02FA9F" blockId="26.[533,1535,484,1480]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FDB4D36FBDD6FC97" bold="true" box="[565,669,797,821]" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Remarks:</emphasis>
Andersen [
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB3B98FF84FF98FC9BD36FBC0BFC97" author="Andersen K." box="[794,832,797,821]" journalOrPublisher="Annals Mag Nat Hist." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="374 - 384" part="2" refId="ref42767" refString="117. Andersen K. Diagnoses of new bats of the families Rhinolophidae and Megadermatidae. Annals Mag Nat Hist. 1918; 2: 374 - 384." title="Diagnoses of new bats of the families Rhinolophidae and Megadermatidae" type="journal article" year="1918">117</bibRefCitation>
] first separated 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FC6BD36FBB14FC96" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[1002,1119,797,821]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomona">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FC6BD36FBCB5FC96" box="[1002,1022,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FB8BD36FBB14FC96" box="[1034,1119,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FB12D36FBBB1FC97" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[1171,1274,797,821]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gentilis">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FB12D36FBBECFC96" box="[1171,1191,797,820]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FB33D36FBBB1FC97" box="[1202,1274,797,821]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">gentilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of the noseleaf of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FDDAD332BD9BFCF5" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[603,720,832,856]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomona">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FDDAD332BD24FCF5" box="[603,623,832,855]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FDFAD332BD9BFCF5" box="[635,720,832,855]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu stricto being broader than the noseleaf of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FB4ED332BA7CFCF5" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[1231,1335,831,856]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gentilis">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FB4ED332BBA8FCF5" box="[1231,1251,832,855]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FB6ED34DBA7CFCF5" box="[1263,1335,831,855]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">gentilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Similarly, Corbet and Hill [
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB3B98FF84FF98FDFAD310BDC3FCD8" author="Corbet GB &amp; Hill JE" box="[635,648,866,890]" journalOrPublisher="Oxford: Oxford University Press" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref38080" refString="9. Corbet GB, Hill JE. The mammals of the Indomalayan region: a systematic review. Oxford: Oxford University Press; 1992." title="The mammals of the Indomalayan region: a systematic review" type="book" year="1992">9</bibRefCitation>
] examined ethanol-preserved specimens and commented that 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FAA2D311BADCFCD8" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[1315,1431,866,890]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomona">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FAA2D311BA7CFCD8" box="[1315,1335,867,890]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FAC3D311BADCFCD8" box="[1346,1431,867,890]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu stricto lacked of lateral supplementary leaflets. Likewise, Douangboubpha et al. [
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB3B98FF84FF98FAE7D3F7BA34FC3F" author="Douangboubpha B &amp; Bumrungsri S &amp; Soisook P &amp; Satasook C &amp; Thomas NM &amp; Bates PJ" box="[1382,1407,901,925]" journalOrPublisher="Acta. Chiropt." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="415 - 438" part="12" refId="ref38382" refString="17. Douangboubpha B, Bumrungsri S, Soisook P, Satasook C, Thomas NM, Bates PJ. A taxonomic review of the Hipposideros bicolor species complex and H. pomona (Chiroptera: Hipposideridae) in Thailand. Acta. Chiropt. 2010; 12 (2): 415 - 438." title="A taxonomic review of the Hipposideros bicolor species complex and H. pomona (Chiroptera: Hipposideridae) in Thailand" type="journal article" year="2010">17</bibRefCitation>
] suggested that 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FDC4D3DABDF2FC1D" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[581,697,936,960]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomona">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FDC4D3DABD12FC1D" box="[581,601,936,959]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FDE5D3DABDF2FC1D" box="[612,697,936,959]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu stricto [
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB3B98FF84FF98FCD2D3DABC2BFC62" author="Corbet GB &amp; Hill JE" box="[851,864,936,960]" journalOrPublisher="Oxford: Oxford University Press" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" refId="ref38080" refString="9. Corbet GB, Hill JE. The mammals of the Indomalayan region: a systematic review. Oxford: Oxford University Press; 1992." title="The mammals of the Indomalayan region: a systematic review" type="book" year="1992">9</bibRefCitation>
] may represents at least two species: 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FB66D3DABA10FC1D" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[1255,1371,936,960]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomona">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FB66D3DABBB0FC1D" box="[1255,1275,936,959]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FA87D3DABA10FC1D" box="[1286,1371,936,959]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu stricto (restricted to Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="F34D06F9FF84FF98FC9DD3B8BC1DFC40" box="[796,854,970,994]" name="India" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">India</collectingCountry>
) and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FC13D3B9BCB2FC40" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[914,1017,970,994]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gentilis">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FC13D3B9BCEDFC40" box="[914,934,971,994]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FC30D3B8BCB2FC40" box="[945,1017,970,994]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">gentilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(distributed from north-east 
<collectingCountry id="F34D06F9FF84FF98FAB3D3B8BA21FC40" box="[1330,1386,970,994]" name="India" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">India</collectingCountry>
into Southeast Asia). DNA sequences of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FCD3D39FBC8DFBA6" box="[850,966,1005,1029]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomono">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FCD3D39FBC2DFBA6" box="[850,870,1005,1028]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FCF3D39FBC8DFBA6" box="[882,966,1005,1028]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomono</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
sensu lato from two mitochondrial genes: ND2 and RAG1 fell into two distinct clades in a phylogenetic tree (see 
<figureCitation id="13615AECFF84FF98FB16D462BB80FB8A" box="[1175,1227,1040,1064]" captionStart="Fig 4" captionStartId="18.[500,532,1848,1867]" captionTargetBox="[500,1536,208,1832]" captionTargetId="figure-1@18.[500,1536,208,1832]" captionTargetPageId="18" captionText="Fig 4. Neighbour-joining tree showing all available DNA barcodes for species in family Hipposideridae reported from Peninsular Malaysia. The percentage of pseudoreplicate trees (±70%) in which the DNA barcodes clustered together in the bootstrap test (500 pseudoreplicates) are shown above the branches. Abbreviation as follows: PM = Peninsular Malaysia,VN = Vietnam, BN = Borneo (including Sabah &amp; Sarawak of East Malaysia, Brunei and Kalimantan Indonesia), TH = Thailand, LA = Laos, SM = Sumatera Indonesia, CH = China, CM = Cambodia. https://doi.org/10.1371/journal.pone.0179555.g004" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4251362" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4251362/files/figure.png" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">
Fig 
<quantity id="4CA2EB8CFF84FF98FB3FD462BB80FB8A" box="[1214,1227,1040,1064]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.016" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" unit="in" value="4.0">4</quantity>
</figureCitation>
in [
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB3B98FF84FF98FB74D462BA50FB8A" author="Murray SW &amp; Campbell P &amp; Kingston T &amp; Zubaid A &amp; Francis CM &amp; Kunz TH" box="[1269,1307,1040,1064]" journalOrPublisher="Mol Phylogenet Evol." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="597 - 611" part="62" refId="ref43062" refString="125. Murray SW, Campbell P, Kingston T, Zubaid A, Francis CM, Kunz TH. Molecular phylogeny of hipposiderid bats from Southeast Asia and evidence of cryptic diversity. Mol Phylogenet Evol. 2012; 62 (2): 597 - 611. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2011.10.021 PMID: 22079552" title="Molecular phylogeny of hipposiderid bats from Southeast Asia and evidence of cryptic diversity" type="journal article" year="2012">125</bibRefCitation>
]): (i) 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FAD8D462BA86FB85" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[1369,1485,1040,1064]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomona">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FAD8D462BA26FB85" box="[1369,1389,1040,1063]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FAF9D462BA86FB85" box="[1400,1485,1040,1063]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FA58D462BD1EFBE8" authorityName="Francis, Kock &amp; Habersetzer" authorityYear="1999" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="rotalis">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FA58D462BAA6FB85" box="[1497,1517,1040,1063]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FD94D440BD1EFBE8" box="[533,597,1074,1098]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">rotalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FD0AD441BC11FBE8" authorityName="Guillen-Servent &amp; Francis" authorityYear="2006" box="[651,858,1074,1098]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="khaokhouayensis">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FD0AD441BDD4FBE8" box="[651,671,1075,1098]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FD2BD440BC11FBE8" box="[682,858,1074,1098]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">khaokhouayensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F34D06F9FF84FF98FC1DD440BC84FBE8" box="[924,975,1074,1098]" name="Laos" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Laos</collectingCountry>
, and (ii) 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FBACD441BBE9FBE8" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[1069,1186,1074,1098]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomona">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FBACD441BB0AFBE8" box="[1069,1089,1075,1098]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FBCCD441BBE9FBE8" box="[1101,1186,1075,1098]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="F34D06F9FF84FF98FB62D440BA5DFBE8" box="[1251,1302,1074,1098]" name="Laos" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Laos</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34D06F9FF84FF98FAA1D440BA28FBE8" box="[1312,1379,1074,1098]" name="China" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">China</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F34D06F9FF84FF98FAECD440BA9DFBE8" box="[1389,1494,1074,1098]" name="Myanmar" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Myanmar</collectingCountry>
and Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="F34D06F9FF84FF98FD3DD427BC56FBCF" box="[700,797,1109,1133]" name="Malaysia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
. Specimens of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FC39D427BB66FBCE" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[952,1069,1109,1133]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomona">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FC39D427BC87FBCE" box="[952,972,1109,1132]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FC59D427BB66FBCE" box="[984,1069,1109,1132]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from both groups are morphologically similar [
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB3B98FF84FF98FDC6D40ABD26FB32" author="Murray SW &amp; Campbell P &amp; Kingston T &amp; Zubaid A &amp; Francis CM &amp; Kunz TH" box="[583,621,1144,1168]" journalOrPublisher="Mol Phylogenet Evol." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="597 - 611" part="62" refId="ref43062" refString="125. Murray SW, Campbell P, Kingston T, Zubaid A, Francis CM, Kunz TH. Molecular phylogeny of hipposiderid bats from Southeast Asia and evidence of cryptic diversity. Mol Phylogenet Evol. 2012; 62 (2): 597 - 611. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ympev. 2011.10.021 PMID: 22079552" title="Molecular phylogeny of hipposiderid bats from Southeast Asia and evidence of cryptic diversity" type="journal article" year="2012">125</bibRefCitation>
]. Three subspecies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FCD6D40ABC87FB2D" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[855,972,1144,1168]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomona">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FCD6D40ABC20FB2D" box="[855,875,1144,1167]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FCF6D40ABC87FB2D" box="[887,972,1144,1167]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have been reported from 
<collectingCountry id="F34D06F9FF84FF98FB5FD40ABA69FB32" box="[1246,1314,1144,1168]" name="China" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">China</collectingCountry>
: 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FAAAD40ABA74FB2D" box="[1323,1343,1144,1167]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FACBD40ABA1CFB2D" box="[1354,1367,1144,1167]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">p</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FAE2D40ABAEFFB2D" box="[1379,1444,1144,1167]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">sinesis</emphasis>
(Min- Guang coastal region), 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FC8AD4E9BCC0FB10" authorityName="K. Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[779,907,1178,1202]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="gentilis">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FC8AD4E9BC54FB10" box="[779,799,1179,1202]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FCABD4E9BC7CFB10" box="[810,823,1179,1202]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">p</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FCC2D4E8BCC0FB10" box="[835,907,1178,1202]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">gentilis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(South 
<collectingRegion id="499E888BFF84FF98FC5ED4E8BBC9FB10" box="[991,1154,1178,1202]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Yunnan region</collectingRegion>
) and an undescribed subspecies (
<collectingRegion id="499E888BFF84FF98FD9CD4CFBD25FB77" box="[541,622,1213,1237]" country="China" name="Hainan" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Hainan</collectingRegion>
Island), showing 6.0–8.5% divergences in cytochrome 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FB35D4CFBB8AFB77" box="[1204,1217,1213,1237]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">b</emphasis>
mtDNA and 5.2–8.0% divergences in COI mtDNA [
<bibRefCitation id="EFCB3B98FF84FF98FC99D492BC75FB5A" author="Zhao LZ &amp; Bu YZ &amp; Zhou HX &amp; Zhou HW &amp; Zhang ZS &amp; Niu HX" box="[792,830,1248,1272]" journalOrPublisher="J Mammal." pageId="26" pageNumber="27" pagination="1305 - 1316" part="96" refId="ref43773" refString="144. Zhao LZ, Bu YZ, Zhou HX, Zhou HW, Zhang ZS, Niu HX. Differences in Hipposideros pomona from three geographical regions in China based on morphology and molecular sequences data. J Mammal. 2015; 96 (6): 1305 - 1316." title="Differences in Hipposideros pomona from three geographical regions in China based on morphology and molecular sequences data" type="journal article" year="2015">144</bibRefCitation>
]. Due to the lack of DNA barcodes from Peninsular 
<collectingCountry id="F34D06F9FF84FF98FAEAD492BA82FB5A" box="[1387,1481,1248,1272]" name="Malaysia" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">Malaysia</collectingCountry>
and unresolved taxonomy across the whole Southeast Asia region, we tentatively retained the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C5A3DEAFF84FF98FD94D554BDC1FA9F" authorityName="Andersen" authorityYear="1918" box="[533,650,1317,1341]" class="Mammalia" family="Hipposideridae" genus="Hipposideros" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="26" pageNumber="27" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pomona">
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FD94D554BD62FA9F" box="[533,553,1318,1341]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B92E9A7BFF84FF98FDB4D554BDC1FA9F" box="[565,650,1318,1341]" italics="true" pageId="26" pageNumber="27">pomona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in this checklist pending further research.
</paragraph>
